{
  "name": "Locus: Aerial Prowess",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to a piece of jewelry.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>This gilded feather has its tips encased in brass.</p><p>While attuned, the relic merges magically merges with a piece of <strong>jewelry (ring, brooch, amulet, necklace, etc.) </strong>of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, and requires 10 minutes to complete. Upon completion, the item takes on the appearance of a brass feather curled upon itself. Once completed, the jewelry becomes magical.</p><p><strong>Effect: </strong>If the attuned creature has a flying speed or one of their familiars or steeds or companions (such as a beastmaster hunter's companion) has a flying speed they can use their <strong>Bonus Action</strong> to move using their flying speed. Additionally, if the ability to fly is lost then they fall as if under the effects of @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplFeatherFal]{Feather Fall} for up to 1 minute.</p>",
